column1: Baby Barnaby's////Come early if you want to eat here
column2: and prepare to wait in line for at least 30 minutes. Walk into the patio and put your name on the waiting list on the hanging notepad. Then you have to wait outside and listen for your name to be called. Food was okay. I don't understand what the hype was all about this place or why there is always a line here. I ordered the steak and eggs sunny side up with potatoes and my girlfriend ordered the green eggs. The steak wasn't tender
column3: but edible. The green eggs were good
column5: I would not wait 30+ minutes in line again here for the food. The only thing good here was the service.
